text: Poor <@U3QMCLQQG> still with the group hug
I think you're just scared to face a well-built hug deck.
I reject the premise it exists. I don’t doubt the deck works, I just don’t buy it works because of the hug elements
What’s one hug card in the deck?
Font of Mythos.
Dictate of Kruphix/Karametra.

Font is perfect. If people are letting you keep a Font in play because they think that’s helping them you can beat them with any stock precon because their understanding of the game mechanics and threat is so terrible. It’s the equivalent of beating first graders in basketball at that point. And if the deck is built to gain a huge asymmetrical benefit from the card as to not care what anyone else gains them it’s not even group hug. It’s like calling Arcane Denial group hug in that situation. So I reject your premise :)
It’s like calling Nekusar hug because everyone draws.
Now maybe my definition of hug is narrower than everyone else.
I always define it as a deck designed to take advantage of people’s reaction to your deck doing things they rightly or wrongly see as helping them.

So if a deck is built to take huge asymmetrical advantage of cards that happen to do beneficial things for other people that to me isn’t hug. The Concordant Crossroads I run is designed to be played in a way that’s asymmetrically advantageous to me so I wouldn’t call it a hug card since nobody is supposed to believe it’s helping them and react accordingly, and if they did then that’s pretty terrible re: their grasp of a lot of things.
Maybe. But I am beating everyone with hug cards. Even though I am gaining insane asymmetrical advantage
Then at least by how I view hug that’s not a hug deck, it’s a deck full of Crossroads.
So by your definition a hug deck is only a hug deck if it equalizes everyone
Or at least cares about the perception that you’re helping.
I try for that with new players, or people who haven't played against the deck before.
It works in those situations.
Otherwise my Edric deck is hugs.
The thing is: the deck often generates bigger threats than one or two individual hug pieces because it ramps people into Ulamog and Sheoldred.
It's a similar deal with Phyrexian Arena
Is that the intent? Because me Edric deck gets greedy players to not swing at me on occasion but I’m not gonna call that part of my strat
Yes, definitely.
If I can pull heat off of me by letting everyone else do their big scary things then I've cinched the game.
Even then I still think it’s relying on people being bad at Magic if the strat is to rely on people not getting you’re the reason Ulamog got out in the first place.
In that case they have to stop or show me before I can let player B get their Ulamog out
I just don’t think hoping your opponents are bad is a way to build a deck, because if they’re bad anything beats them
